# Privacy Policy

**Last updated:** February 2025

Rhythm ("we", "our", or "the app") is a circadian rhythm and focus tracking app. This privacy policy explains what data we collect, how we use it, and your rights regarding your information.

---

## 1. Data We Collect

### Account Information
When you create an account, we collect:
- **Email address** – for authentication and account recovery
- **Name** – if you provide it (e.g. via Sign in with Apple or during sign-up)
- **Account credentials** – stored securely by our authentication provider

### Health & Activity Data
To provide circadian rhythm insights and focus tracking, we collect:
- **Sleep data** – bed time, wake time, duration, and sleep quality
- **Energy levels** – your self-reported energy across the day
- **Mood and focus scores** – when you log study or activity sessions
- **Study logs** – minutes studied, subject, and optional notes

### Goals & Experiments
- **Daily goals** – titles, descriptions, and completion status
- **Experiment participation** – which experiments you run and task completion
- **Learned insights** – summaries generated from your experiment data

### Technical Data
- **Push notification tokens** – if you enable reminders, we store your device token to send notifications
- **Timezone** – to correctly display and schedule your data

---

## 2. How We Use Your Data

We use your data to:
- **Provide the app** – sync your logs, goals, and experiments across devices
- **Calculate your circadian rhythm** – generate personalised focus curves from your sleep and energy data
- **Send reminders** – if you opt in, send push notifications at your chosen time
- **Improve the service** – run experiments and insights that help you understand your patterns

We do **not** sell your data to third parties.

---

## 3. Third-Party Services

We use the following services to operate the app:

| **Supabase** | Database, authentication, serverless functions | Account info, all logged data |
| **Expo** | Push notifications | Device push token only |

These providers process data on our behalf under their own privacy policies. Supabase is hosted in the cloud; data may be stored in regions outside your country.

---

## 4. Data Retention

- **Active accounts** – We retain your data while your account is active.
- **Deleted accounts** – When you delete your account, we permanently remove your account and all associated data (profiles, sleep logs, study logs, goals, experiments, push subscriptions) from our systems. Deletion is typically completed within a short period.

---

## 5. Your Rights

You can:
- **Access your data** – View and export your data within the app.
- **Correct your data** – Edit logs, goals, and profile information at any time.
- **Delete your account** – Use "Delete account" in Profile → Account. This permanently removes all your data.

If you are in the UK, EU, or EEA, you may also have rights to data portability, restriction of processing, and to lodge a complaint with your data protection authority.

---

## 6. Security

We use industry-standard security practices:
- Authentication via Supabase Auth (secure, encrypted)
- Row-level security so you can only access your own data
- HTTPS for all network traffic

---

## 7. Children

Rhythm is not intended for users under 13. We do not knowingly collect data from children under 13. If you believe we have collected such data, please contact us and we will delete it.

---

## 8. Changes to This Policy

We may update this policy from time to time. We will notify you of material changes by updating the "Last updated" date and, where appropriate, through the app. Continued use of the app after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.

---

## 9. Contact Us

If you have questions about this privacy policy or your data, contact us at:

